<subSubSection pageId="57" pageNumber="58" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="57.[151,1437,1286,1637]" pageId="57" pageNumber="58">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,1539,1565]" pageId="57" pageNumber="58">Remarks.</emphasis>
The species misidentified and figured in 
<bibRefCitation author="Remes Lenicov, A. M. &amp; Paradell, S. L." box="[775,1156,1539,1565]" pageId="57" pageNumber="58" pagination="263 - 269" refId="ref81130" refString="Remes Lenicov, A. M. &amp; Paradell, S. L. (2009) Argentinean species of the Faltala leafhopper group (Hemiptera: Cicadellidae: Deltocephalinae). Revista de la Sociedad Entomologica Argentina, 68, 263 - 269." type="journal article" year="2009">Remes Lenicov &amp; Paradell (2009)</bibRefCitation>
as 
<taxonomicName box="[1192,1344,1539,1565]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Faltala" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="57" pageNumber="58" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="furcipennis">
<emphasis box="[1192,1344,1539,1565]" italics="true" pageId="57" pageNumber="58">F. furcipennis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
appears to represent an undescribed species with some similarity in the shape of the aedeagus to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Zahniser" authorityYear="2021" box="[1158,1311,1575,1601]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Faltala" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="57" pageNumber="58" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="catalanoae">
<emphasis box="[1158,1311,1575,1601]" italics="true" pageId="57" pageNumber="58">F. catalanoae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
but differs significantly in the shape of the male pygofer and female sternite VII.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
